Class AggregationA

java.lang.Object

                  evs.gui.windows.AggregationA
All Implemented Interfaces:
GUICommunicator, GUIInterface, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible
public class AggregationA
extends javax.swing.JPanel
implements GUIInterface

The first aggregation window where the user manages spatial aggregation units and their associated attributes. In this context, an aggregation unit is a set of river segments with common parameters (time-series and environmental variable IDs among others).

Version:
4.0
Author:
evs@hydrosolved.com
See Also:
Serialized Form

saveData

public boolean saveData()
                 throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
Attempts to save the local parameter values to aggregation units. Throws an exception if any of the input parameters are undefined or take incorrect values. This is a local save for the current window. TODO: store the local parameters in an indexed HashMap, following the implementation in VerificationA.java, rather than an Object array with assumed index structure.
